-- Brioni Roman Style Promotes Francesco Pesci to Chief Executive Officer
-- B y   A n d r e w   R o b e r t s
-- 2010-11-09T19:11:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/brioni-roman-style-promotes-francesco-pesci-to-chief-executive-officer.html
Brioni Roman Style SpA , whose suits
have been worn by  Clark Gable  and James Bond, said it promoted
Francesco Pesci to chief executive officer.  The appointment of Pesci, who was previously commercial
director, is effective immediately, Penne, Italy-based Brioni
said today in a statement.  General Manager  Antonio Bianchini  had been handling the
day-to-day running of the suitmaker since  Andrea Perrone , the
grandson of Brioni co-founder  Gaetano Savini , resigned as CEO in
July.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Andrew Roberts  in Paris at 
 Aroberts36@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 